cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with interpretations over relational structures and uses weak monadic second-order logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper specifically investigates the expressive power of set interpretations applied to infinite deterministic trees. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the decidability of theories before and after applying set interpretations. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with finite sets and their properties. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also possible as the results of the paper can be used in the study of automatic and tree-automatic structures.
